%N A397972 Lower (1,1/3) midsequence of triangular numbers (A000217) and squares (A000290); see Comments.
%C A397972 Suppose that s = (s(n)) and t = (t(n)) are sequences of numbers and h > 0 and k > 0. The lower (h, k)-midsequence of s and t is floor(h*s + k*t); the upper (h, k)-midsequence of s and t is ceiling(h*s + k*t). Guide to (r,s) midsequences of triangular numbers and squares:
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1,1/2):  A035608 (lower), A171769 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1,1/3):  A397972 (lower), A397973 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1,2/3):  A397974 (lower), A397975 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1,3/2):  A397976 (lower), A397977 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1/2,1):  A397978 (lower), A397979 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1/3,1):  A397980 (lower), A397981 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(2/3,1):  A397982 (lower), A397983 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(3/2,1):  A397984 (lower), A397985 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1/2,1/3):  A397986 (lower), A397987 (upper)
%C A397972 (r,s)=(1/3,1/2):  A397988 (lower), A397989 (upper)
